{
  "texts": [
    "It compares predicted labels to real labels and shows different classification outcomes.",
    "The confusion matrix reveals model performance.",
    "True positives (TP) and true negatives (TN) are situations that were accurately predicted.",
    "False positives (FP) and false negatives (FN) are cases of misclassification.",
    "These values allow us to generate model performance metrics including accuracy, precision, recall, and F1 score."
  ]
}